Description.
Ocellar triangle dark brown, with ca. 1 or 2 seta(e) above ocellar setae. Frons brownish (
Fig. 5G
). Pedicel brownish yellow; first flagellomere yellow (
Fig. 5G
). Clypeus brownish yellow medially and brownish laterally. Palpus brownish (
Fig. 5G
). Postpronotal lobe yellow (
Fig. 5I
). Acrostichal setulae in ca. 12–14 irregular rows (
Fig. 5H
). Scutellum brownish yellow to brownish, brown to dark brown laterally, yellow at tip (
Fig. 5H
). Pleura with a brown, longitudinal stripe above (
Fig. 5H
). Katepisternum and mesopleuron mostly yellowish to yellow (
Fig. 5I
). Wing (
Fig. 2C
): Costal vein between R and R 
4+5
distally with ca. 5 or 6 peg-like spinules on ventral surface; R 
4+5
and M 
1
nearly parallel distally; halter mostly yellowish, with a brownish yellow patch at knob (
Fig. 5H
). Abdominal tergites black, 2nd tergite yellow medially and laterally, 3rd tergite not shortened in males (
Fig. 9D, E
), yellow anteriorly, sometimes also yellow laterally, 4th tergite yellow anteriorly. Male terminalia: Epandrium lacking pubescence, with ca. 7 setae near posterior margin per side (
Fig. 19A
). Cercus lacking pubescence (
Fig. 19A
). Surstylus pubescent (
Fig. 19A
). Paramere narrow basally, with ca. 6 sensilla distally (
Fig. 19C
).
